TASK.DESCRIPTION:
In case there are no PBMDW files to process for EITHER the RXC or RUC feeds, this command will re-generate (mainly for first time in region) an empty byte file, and then put the name of that empty byte file into BOTH the RXC and RUC indirect filenames that were written out by the previous session. If the previous session build an empty file for that feed, this will prevent the feed from abending for not finding at least one filename in the indirect file it reads.
Added as part of ITPR020090 Rebates PBMDW Migration in July 2017
TASK.NAME: CMD_UNIX_Build_Empty_Entry
